The paper deals with computational geometry and algorithms for computing the volume of the union of boxes in d-dimensional space. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses reductions and complexity theory, which are related to data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
